The enroulement and violence "forms within the internal to the same extent.
The timber copy in waves executives of windows, the balustrades, decorative elements, the oeilleton and slats.
The house Battlo which exists in the neighborhood Eixample in the street market Passeig of Gracia. 43, was born of a house of 1877 of the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction within two years and the house ended in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, initially insisted on the demolition of the vieile construction and the construction of another any new but quickly accepted the idea of a proper talk of reconstruction unusual and cheaper.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as house multiple was not thought to have a proper talk alone.
