The devices to follow people are increasingly demanded by parents who want to monitor their children.
The fear for their child brings more people to watch a GPS.
The system, set up in the early to seek cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases by exmple as that of the small Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a box of matches but will soon be the size of a show.
The case of the small Anicka has moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to confuse their privacy.
"we are trying to tell everyone that it is not a spy but only one way to reduce the likelihood that there will be another tragedy," said Petr Pilin society MAcro Weil, who is one of the suppliers of tracing the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet met such cases."
"the majority of people are really customers who buy the product for security reasons, Pilin adds.
According to him the children should always know what is used "the container" and how to use in case of emergency.
The psychologist for children, Dana Bockova, draws attention if the child does not want to focus on something of this kind, he débarassera.
'And even smaller can be very creative when it comes to getting rid of express something when they do not want to be under control ."
"mobile phones, which can be cut as these devices tracing, have already led parents to many expectations," says Bockova.
She said the fact that this type of device can help in the event of an attack is highly questionable.
"if it is an abduction, the author will do everything so that the child has no electronic device that can locate him."
"it is now the phone."
"that will develop devices tracing, they (criminals) will seek also because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"in such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police," said the psychologist.
She acknowledged that such devices can help during an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech society RC Monitoring, which offers services tracing both for cars and people, claims to have this kind of apparatus can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an attack.
"the device could be paramétré in such a way that it is in regular issuance after a certain period."
"in the case where the aircraft is destroyed, it remains the last position of the person concerned."
'The appliances more expensive also have an inclinomètre who immediately reported the position of the person who had slipped and finds himself in a recumbent position without taking any action, "said Cech.
According to him the so-called smart phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer comparable service after formaté with a prologiciel special.
The problem of systems of tracing current is that it is a device similar to those they wear in pendentif the size of a box of matches or the smaller telephone.
We can always lose.
According to Pilina society Macro Weil, that is why the tests are being conducted to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"this will have the advantage that the possible aggressor will not recognize the apparatus of tracing."
"or it will show, after some time, which would have given the police a little more time," he said.
When the tracing is developed in the form of bracelet or pendentif, it utilisiera always the same technology to make cars.
It is a combination of systems of acquiring a position via GPS (which is commonly used in autonavigation) and a function of a cell phone alert the current position of a vehicle.
The army has so many cordeaux détonants could do the Czech Republic with. but it can take two years.
The army has purchased 445 km of cordeaux used for explosives.
Last year the Ministry of Defence had bought 224 km.
The army has reservations for 225 years.
