The fishermen living in the small town nearby Bodo must now pull for six hours to reach the fishing grounds: The country Ogoni located at the heart of the Niger Delta is regarded as one of the most polluted in the world.
The full extent of the devastation Barnavi leafing through the marshes of mangrove forests by the waters.
