The director of the IAEA, Mr Yukiya Amano, who had to propose these inspections, has already spoken of "an option that I am open to the future," but it is still.
This means entails a huge risk: on the one hand, it requires a majority on the Board of Governors of the IAEA and many of the 35 countries represented there have no desire to see the situation escalate.
On the other hand, as this diplomat who gives réflechir: "At this point, if in the end they do not find anything"
