Zapatero and the red line German
Berlin has opted to remain in the euro, but it establishes the conditions for the entire Union.
The tension of the markets have caused a doble government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new methods of adjustment, which vary from tax cuts for the SMEs, regulation of private placement or removal of 426 euros to help the unemployed without work to the privatisation of the 49% AENA, airport management Barajas and El Prat and 30% of Loteries state.
On the other, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of former president Felipe González, the criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel on its responsibility to the current crisis.
How are these movements?
It should be noted that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its forthcoming policy.
On the contrary, it is a further restriction of the difficult process of redefinition of the euro.
And here Germany has a radically new vision of its future, which shocked with the need to maintain the old traditions of most of its partners.
In the face of resistance in Europe, in Germany we have begun to speculate on the three possible out of the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the south would abandon the currency zone.
The second, the recovery of Mark, even if it sounds of science fiction, with a body of opinion very favourable, nearly a 50% of the population.
The third, a new design of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater macroeconomic control, budgetary rigour, fines on countries which contravene the possible suspension of payments of an and extension to the private sector costs of potential adjustments.
The German position is clear and it's been a long time that it is, therefore, now there is no place for excuses.
First, in 2009, when both the IMF and the European Commission were deficits, the German Government has invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first signal of divergence between what Germany felt that we had to do (plans of fiscal stringency and stability of public finances) and its European partners, ci-inclut France, used.
The second of the Central European countries was when Merkel has extended the difficult decision to save Greece.
From then on it was the subject of a fierce criticism, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and public opinion and the CommunityTrade were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel expressed a clear position, asking the reform of the Treaties of the Union to make possible the rescue of a country and force at the same time the private lenders to bear the cost.
This has been interpreted as anti-European, because it has precipitated the Irish crisis and the rest.
But his proposal, although a bit weaker, has been approved, and the following month, we should see the process of reform of the Union which makes possible these measures from 2013.
Germany has laid out a red line that she does not think fold.
And she tells us that, even if we must take measures with which it may not be too agree, as of this date where the former functioning of the euro would have ended.
2013 will see the birth of a new monetary zone, in which countries which contravene the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to be declared in default and, in this case, the private sector will also be a party of costs.
Germany tells us that we must follow a tough path of growth with high rates of savings and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and external balances positive.
An alternative based on debt and construction, with huge holes in the balance of payments, such as the one who has chaired the Spanish growth in the years of boom, will simply not be tolerated.
The setting is clear.
And it would be wrong not to hear it.
It is not only to renew the public deficit to 3% in 2013.
What we demand is much harder.
And what they must not do in these circumstances is to deceive oneself.
I hope that the current turbulence leave happen to us a greater tranquillity.
And learn to seize the opportunity that we were given, until the spring of 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero has also heard of this form and its dual statement (the reforms promised after the past Saturday with large companies and yesterday's announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, it opened the way to the argument that we need to bring order to the house.
But the red line that Germany has outlined is, and they do not seem to move.
And among the possibilities that, we cannot exclude that to abandon a monetary zone too full of countries which are not serious.
And in this case, we can always say it had warned.
Sport and fraud law
The game similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax show ingenuity but not the desire to escape punishment.
The expulsion conversation in principle by two players from Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) during the match of 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League has caused rivers of ink on the anti-sportif nature of such behaviour and if both players should be punished by UEFA.
As you know, a few minutes before the game that their team already earned clearly), the two players have deliberately lost time when they have made mistakes in determining the referee to show them the second yellow card.
As well, and Real Madrid will eventually be leader of his group, the two players will sanction the regulatory during the match next match against Auxerre dam and can pass without cards to the next phase.
Finally, the discipline of UEFA has punished with two matches the coach of the team, José Mourinho and various economic players are involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in circumstances like this or similar is not a new practice, if not more frequent in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos, of Asia, but followed, of the sport.
Part of the debate in the case told is due to the fact that this was as a team of the entity of Real Madrid (which in its anthem poster noblemen and honor and that in times past was fined for its players for similar conduct) and the dramatization orchestrated, it seems, by Mourinho, which adds an episode of its history of inflated technician histrionique and provocative.
In any case, the debate was asked if this type of behavior not expressly prohibited by the regulation contradicts the principles of sport, i.e., if with committing fraud bill; because they are environmentally actions with the rules of sport, but seem to evade its meaning.
The question is to examine the type of damage they cause to the sporting spirit.
A property which includes the sporting spirit is the physical integrity of opposing players, an aspect that with these actions has not been put at risk, that is, there has been no violent game.
Another of these goods that we talk with the game right is preventing the team players infracteurs benefits in an unfair manner contrary to the team, which is not the case either.
However, the paradox of the actions of the players of the Real Madrid is that it is best not to what is normally characterised as cheating or fraud of the law, because its violation of the rules has not been conducted behind closed doors to try to avoid punishment, but their action has tried to be as clear as possible to receive the penalisation of the referee.
They expected and they have gladly accepted the sanction.
Another issue is the kind of advantage that infracteurs receive the well-meaning examined.
Here it seems necessary to see that we are not in a situation of disadvantage to rival and has an advantage in the same match either, because obviously the result of the action means leaving their own team with fewer players.
And this is not an useful strategy for the next game either, because the club could not count on these players.
Of course, the advantage is that the players will begin the next phase of the Champions' League without cards that could threaten their participation in a future.
But this is a long-term benefit, with a degree of ambiguity, because the team could be eliminated suddenly and apart from that, with this action players perform a sanction and move into the second round of boxes, in which the suspension due to the accumulation of cards with a less than in the first round.
So, climb to the top, it is not clear if that is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the spirit of sport, which is still part strategic decision-making that promote maximum advantage from this that the rules allow.
In our case, the players have not set up to avoid the application of the penalty that would indeed be a clear case of fraud), otherwise they chose instead the moment in which they are subjected to it.
They made a strategic decision without disrupting the penalty or flee.
Even if the line between genius and fraud is widespread in this opportunity I think that we have had a clear case of genius.
The controversy, I think, is due to two factors: because there were two auto-expulsions and because of how the director for the cause.
The harm caused to the principles of sport by these actions is not all ethical and aesthetic.
