China maintains the goals to reduce greenhouse gases
The representative of the country in the COP16 assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and explained that it maintains its offer to cut up to 2020 between 40 and 45 percent of its greenhouse gas emissions.
China maintains its offer to cut between 40 and 45 percent of greenhouse gas emissions before 2020, Su Wei, representative of the country in COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16 th Conference of the Parties to the Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and redeploy its industry.
In fact, has exposé-t-il, the last four years the country has inverti $245 million in efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
Nevertheless, it is clear that China will not change its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
He said that the Chinese strategy in the field of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; building capacity; construction of institutions and support for pilot programs.
There has been progress in all these areas, ci-inclut approval last year, a new Act of Energy, which recognizes the objectives addressed in the reduction of greenhouse gases, has expliqué-t-il.
On the other hand, he pointed out that in China, federal authorities have worked in a coordinated manner with the government and local to achieve the objectives of saving energy, use energy efficient and reduce emissions.
In addition, has déclaré-t-il, there are various multi-annual plans underway or completed, both funded by the Chinese government and by the governments of other countries.
For example, has mentionné-t-il, the programmeI Efficiente Use of Energy, which has been implémenté during the last five years and has invested in the United Nations (UN), the government and private initiative.
There is also a draft provincial of climate change, another for the change of light bulbs with energy-efficient lamps and another mitigation and adaptation, has détaillé-t-il.
At the same table, Martin Krol, scientific adviser to the government of that country on climate change, has ensured that the efforts of China were larger than what we think.
For example, has exposé-t-il, the per capita emissions of greenhouse gases in China is three tons per person, while the United States it is 100 tonnes; China is responsible for 9% of the historic contribution in the contamination.
Similarly, it has made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how a 20% increase energy efficiency in the last five years and plans to make another similar to 2020, has déclaré-t-il.
