Romano now has an opportunity to no longer be a technician sous-champion and for the first time the glory of the securities.
The European Union is changing the rules for visa
People must go to WCPU for Demandeurs Visa before their interview in the Section Consulaire; the costly waiting time more reduced.
From 10 January 2011 the processing of visa at the Embassy and consulates in the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit to WCPU for Demandeurs Visa (CSA, according to its initials) before their interview in the Section Consulaire.
The CSA will biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Division Consulaire before the interview.
The new procedure will present some benefits for candidates, among which it mentions the following:
The total cost to deal with the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment for an appointment, another payment for the processing and another for the courier service delivers the document.
The aspiring will make a single payment covering the three services.
The tariff will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with demand (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for the visas of traders and investors.
People who want to renew their visas will not go to an interview with the Representative Consulaire, they will be available only to the CSA closer to where they will present papers and we will take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Section Consulaire remain less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to Consulats of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey, Nuevo Laredo cannot pay the extra fee of 26 dollars.
For more information on the new procedure to apply for the visa, visit the following page http: / / / / mexico.usembassy.gov boletines sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
NASA announced the discovery of extraterrestrial life
The space agency of the United States has cited the press for presenting a discovery that will impact on the research of living in the area.
The administration of the National Aeronautics and Space (NASA) of the United States will supply tomorrow, Thursday, a discovery astrobiologique, which could prove the theory of the existence of extraterrestrial life.
The discovery will be presented in a press conference on Thursday at 13: 00 p.m. at NASA headquarters in Washington to experts astrobiology, science on the origin, development, distribution and future of life in the universe.
When she quoted the press, NASA has assured that it will issue which will impact on the search for extraterrestrial life ," which has sparked speculation by experts from other countries.
The discovery could prove the theory that there are creatures similar to us and in ambient hostile was uninhabited and would put on the table the possibility of becoming intelligent beings as humans if living conditions have improved.
It seems that there is talk of a microbe discovered at the bottom of the Mono Lake in the Yosemite National Park, California, who lives in a narrative that it was too poisonous for any form of life, because the lake is rich in arsénique.
In any form, the creature uses the arsénique as a way of life and this capacity suggests that a similar life could exist on other planets that do not have our atmosphere.
According to the astrobiologistes, if these organizations use the arsénique in their metabolism, this proves that "there is another form of life, a second form of life, different than we are."
The space agency will contact the true scope of discoveries in the press conference tomorrow, Thursday.
The conference will attend the géobiologie Pamela Conrad, who is studying the possibility of life on Mars; and the biologist Steven Benner, one of the scientists who study Titan (the largest satellite of Saturn), in that its chemistry is similar to that of the Earth.
