14 suspected drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were conducted in the Eastern Townships, Wednesday, in the framework of the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people were arrested and will face various charges.
The searches were conducted in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that were used in the production of drugs.
"about 750 cannabis plants, four kilograms of hashish, money and equipment used in the production were seized," said Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesman of the Sûreté du Quebec.
In total, eleven men and three women were arrested, including two heads Theaterfrauen alleged of this network, two men of Sherbrooke.
Those arrested were to appear at the courthouse to Sherbrooke in the hours after their arrest.
They could face charges of cannabis production, possession for the purpose of trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches took place following an investigation, which lasted almost a year.
"this is information received from the public which has enabled us to make these arrests," said Mr. Ruel.
Some 70 police CIHROperating regional investigation in the Eastern Townships of the Sûreté du Québec, the Police Service of Sherbrooke and the Régie police Memphrémagog, took part in this operation.
