The criticism of the NPD on immigration, Olivia Chow, has discounted the criticism that his party is not tough enough on illegal immigrants.
"the New Democrats agree to take measures against smugglers of illegal and that is what we are doing through another bill, C- 35," said Mrs Chow.
"we do not support the bill conservatives because it takes to refugees and imprisons children for at least a year," said Mrs Chow.
The immigration minister, Jason Kenney, has accused opposition parties of playing the politics and to ignore the will of Canadians.
