Rivers under strict surveillance
Several rivers remain under special supervision because of heavy rain in several regions of the province since Tuesday.
A landslide occurred Wednesday afternoon, in Shawinigan, in the Mauricie region.
Two homes have been evacuated preemptively.
In the evening, another shift would have happened to Saint-Lin-Laurentides, in Lanaudière.
A road is collapsing.
From Tuesday to Wednesday evening, heavy rain in several regions, from 40 to 70 millimetres of rain.
From 20 to 40 millimetres of rain additional were expected by Thursday evening, according to the regions.
The sectors in the north of the river and in the Valley were most affected.
They could receive up to 100 millimetres of rain.
As add these rainfall to the melting of the snow already accumulated in some sectors, the spillover of several rivers.
