The Montréal of Algerian origin Nacereddine Zemmal was hellishly particular.
The athlete who excels in "sanda" (kung-fu "full contact"), in kickboxing and Thai boxing gets on the tatamis and rings the world in search of new challenges.
"I've just started the martial arts as kung-fu and the kickboxing 12 years ago, in Algeria, explained Zemmal, installed in the mainland since 2008 for change among professionals."
"in my case, I'm fighting everywhere, as for those who do not like the game on the ground now, mixed martial arts competitions are rare in North America."
Recently, one who works as a security officer and as committed to the company UPS has just issued bad news to his rivals, he won two gold medals in the finals of the world amateur of the World Karate and Kickboxing Association (WKA), from 23 to 30 October, in Edinburgh, Scotland.
"I won the categories of kickboxing full contact and Thai boxing, he explained."
"currently, I am preparing to go to China for the World Cup san shou."
"the fighters who have finished in the first four at the last World Cup in each category were invited."
"I won the bronze in 2009 in Toronto."
"in 2005, Vietnam, I finished eighth."
"in 2007, in China, I have concluded the tournament in the fifth, when I came in third in Toronto in 2009, he added."
"what is interesting is that I have made to each competition."
"at this rate, I will be the first time or next year!"
The "san shou" or "sanda" is a discipline from China where fisticuffs and, in that the projections are allowed.
The duels take place (s) on a platform and more rarely in a ring.
The pugiliste most renowned resulting from this form of struggle is the American of Vietnamese origin Cung The, well known around the world of martial arts.
If Nacer Zemmal has to retain only one event in his career, it will certainly his super tournament "King Sanda," the Super Bowl of kung-fu.
"this competition is the more elevated and the most prestigious in China, explained the sympathetic gaillard."
"this is the equivalent of the Stade Lumpinee (the biggest stage of Thailand)."
"that was a great experience."
Zemmal won his first fight, semi-finals of its category (80 kg), before losing the final.
"I am defeated was a true pro, he analyzed."
"there are four fighters by category (80 kg, 85 kg, 90 kg and 90 kg)."
"the winners of the semi-final advance to a final in their category."
"then, the winners of each category will face to crown a champion, only the king of kung-fu."
450 million in contracts
Hydro-Québec was awarded to $450 million in contracts to firms for the Eastmain- 1 -A-Sarcelle-Rupert hydroelectric project.
At the heart of this avalanche of more than 100 contracts, it is a consortium of firms OPI, Dessau, SM Group and Axor who received the most important, that of the stewardship of the project, for a total of $295 million with no bids.
This consortium called Energy Storage was formed in 2004 associated with the choice of going to the private sector its responsibility to manage this important hydroelectric project of $5 billion.
At the beginning of 2005, the consortium Energy Storage lotteries lucrative contract without competitive bidding.
For the Parti Quebecois, recourse to consortia of enterprises poses a serious ethical problem that threatens to eliminate competition and raise prices.
"this is the new way of making the collusion and to eliminate competition."
"people, instead of doing it in secret, now are open," said yesterday the MP péquiste Sylvain Simard in press conference.
Earlier in the morning, Mr. Simard has raised the issue in the National Assembly because it said difficult to see how the public interest can be used in this way.
The Minister of Natural Resources, Nathalie Normandeau, counters in the afternoon, vigorously denying that there was collusion for this contract.
"I began to have my trip," complaining that the PQ was "dishonest" and had "lacked rigour."
She said that "it would be the least" that is an excuse.
The formula of consortia is a common practice in the world.
It is usually an alliance with a time of two or more companies to merge their respective expertise in order to respond to a call for tenders for a complex project.
The project Eastmain contains a high level of complexity because of the scale of the work.
The site is underway and will continue until 2012.
However, the contract was awarded without competition act; there have been negotiations.
Also, the formula of consortia is no longer an exception in Quebec, even for relatively simple projects.
As revealed last week, Le Devoir the formula of consortia in the sector of the génie-conseil investigated the government.
A quick overview of the register of Quebec firms can now count more than 200 consortia, some of which appear to be permanent.
Thus, the firm Dessau works in partnership with most of its main competitors, including CIMA +, Génivar, PAE and other Roche and Tecsult.
Each combination, and there are dozens, back to the same person moral, Dessau.
As for the consortium Energy Storage, the Minister Normandeau stressed that "the territory of the James Bay responds to the dynamics of manpower and that Hydro-Québec provides a special since the 70 s."
The boss of the project Eastmain, Réal Laporte of Power Corporation of James Bay (SEBJ), gave an explanation that has made strides on the fact that the contract of stewardship of the project has been awarded to achieve.
"if you appeal and there are few bidders, prices will be higher."
"you have two choices: either you take people who are in this market and that you say: we will negotiate a satisfactory and with a good price."
"but the idea is that this is not the price that is important, it is the responsibility of the people," said Mr. Laporte.
The contract awarded to the consortium Energy Storage is part of a long list of contracts over $50 000 in the convention.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec and SEBJ the for the Eastmain- 1 project -A-Sarcelle-Rupert.
After verification, Le Devoir 109 contracts génie-conseil granted between 2002 and March 2010 to companies or their subsidiaries, including laboratories of soil.
PAE has swept 22 contracts, Génivar had 16, 14 and 10 Tecsult Dessau, not to mention his participation in Energy stewardship.
All the contracts were negotiated.
449 783 $344, including the contract to Energy stewardship of 295 131 $564.
Sylvain Simard has hinted that the four firms that make up the consortium (OPI, Dessau, SM Group and Axor) are "well known to the Liberal Party of Quebec."
The minister Normandeau dropped the PQ is also linked to these firms "finance," before it was more of its leaders.
Barometer of responsible consumption - The label "green" does not inspire confidence
Greener, but frankly sceptical.
The consumer Quebecois very little confidence in the players of sustainable development, but also to brands and certification écologisantes to guide their choices.
Worse, even though he lives in a world where media messages for more responsible abound, there is a lack of credible information, deficiency as a brake on its commitment, indicates the Baromètre of responsible consumption, whose first reading was delivered yesterday.
Even if they have increased the consumption of products so-called socially responsible in 2010, Quebeckers seem to make very little credit to those who try to sell them.
Two thirds of them say indeed does not believe the environmental performance of companies like advertising green companies, reveals the measurement tool developed by the Observatory of responsible consumption of the Sherbrooke University.
Another observation: half of doubt on the reliability of official certification of products on the so-called fair, but also of the credibility of products and brands become as parties involved, says the Baromètre.
In the same vein, the politicians' rhetoric on this issue is taken seriously by only 14.6% of Quebeckers.
Information on responsible consumption appears, however, crucial to stimulate this part of the lively currently consumption by almost a third of Quebec consumers.
Indeed, the vacuum and the untrustworthiness of information calmeraient reined in 46% of consumers.
This is the second brake identified by the Baromètre, after the higher price of these products.
Moreover, a third of Quebecers also claim to be well-publicized alleged performance of green products or services that it seeks to put in the hands.
On another note, consumers have been almost half in 2010 to have changed their habit and especially changed brand of one or more products to meet their conviction.
Up to 61%, they have also helped the purchases from traders in their neighbourhood and privileged food grown in their region, says the Baromètre.
More green and responsible - the index of responsible consumption reached 64 on a maximum of 100 for this year - the Homo consumus Quebec likes to present itself as the king of recycling, which seeks to reduce its environmental footprint in ensuring the protection of animals.
But his social conscience and ecological appears, however, remain outside of his car, indicates the Baromètre: in 2010, barely 28% of Quebeckers reported having used public transportation or promoted carpooling to defend their interests.
Walking and cycling have also been supported by 39.1% of the participants in this vast behavioral survey, which has just taken its first cliché.
