The countries that are at the forefront, Portugal and Spain, for their part, are preparing to adopt structural reforms, particularly in relation to the organisation of the labour market.
Reforms which are added to the austerity measures in effect closer.
Lisbon and Madrid want to follow a different path than those of Greece and Ireland.
Both are keen to avoid asking for international assistance before putting in place their own corrections budget and decide on structural reforms needed to restore lasting confidence.
The European lenders, finally, is on the options available to accelerate the process of normalization of sovereign bond markets.
Mark in Paris, on 24 November, Axel Weber had the first proposed the idea that if the EUR 750 billion mobilised by Europe and the International Monetary Fund were not enough, the Union would not hesitate to call the portfolio.
Economists at Barclays Capital, a major market of the European sovereign debt, consider that an increase of around 100 billion euros would be enough, "preferably" in the form of direct injection of liquidity.
The vehicle is: this is the NMWR European financial stabilisation fund which, to date, 60 billion euros.
A council which is likely to be considered carefully in European capitals.
Especially if market conditions have deteriorated.
Snow and ice: 24 departments in vigilance Orange
The episodes neigeux still lead to traffic problems, particularly on the secondary network in Britain, and threaten to disrupt certain economic activities.
Legal-counsel departments are now in Orange vigilance because of the risk of snow and ice.
The Eure, the Eure-et-Loir, Deux-Sèvres and Vienna, have added to the 20 already in vigilance Orange, 18 since Wednesday afternoon and two, the Dordogne and the Gironde, later in the night.
According to Skywatchers France, snow supported the north of the Gironde and Charente and snow low on the Ile-de-France.
Layers of snow from 2 to 5 cm, regularly from 7 to 10 cm, are expected for the departments concerned, and from 1 to 3 cm, or up to 5 cm in the Paris region.
The departments concerned are those of the Charente, Charente-Maritime, Côtes of Armor, six Gironde, Dordogne, Poitou and Basse-Normandie, Ile-de-France and Limousin.
The episodes neigeux are significant enough to cause traffic problems and disrupt certain economic activities, warns Skywatchers France.
In the Côtes of Armor, several district have been banned for lorries of 7.5 tonnes, whose Guingamp-Lannion axes and Saint-Brieuc-Loudéac.
The movement on the secondary network in Britain is very difficult, according to the gendarmes who recommend to take his vehicle that in case of need and the movement of some coaches EU-TER has been suspended for the day.
School transport were banned for Thursday in Picardy.
No specific measures proposed Wednesday evening to restrict the movement of heavy vehicles.
The prefecture "invites all motorists caution on the roads and to adapt their conduct accordingly."
The Directorate General of Civil Aviation (DGAC) has asked the airlines to cancel 25% of their flights on the Paris airport Roissy and 10% to Orly because of snow to come.
The DGAC recommends for air passengers to contact their airline.
In Britain, Gatwick airport, south of London, and Edinburgh, Scotland, are closed until Thursday morning.
